Subject: Re: [T2] Front tire carrier to VW emblem

I'm curious, about some of these front tire mounts.  I've seen lots of the
aftermarket spare tire mounts which just bolt on to the front panel as you've
all described.
Was there a "factory" option for front tire mounting?  If so,
did it mount to the front in the same way?

When I get the time, I'll post
some photos of my front spare mounting.
It was part of the camper conversion
from Viking.

It's a little nicer in that it's an L-shaped piece of sheet
metal.  The bottom of the L is mounted to the top of the front bumper.
At the
top of the L there are two brackets.  The front bracket has the lugs for
mounting the spare.  The rear bracket attaches to the front grille and is
basically used for stability.
So all the load from the wheel and mount is
handled by the bumper.
Maybe in time this will deform the bumper, but it seems
to be of a heavier gauge steel as well as being easier to replace.


Josh
.
