> some folks have
had problems with the metal tearing out and denting from the
weight/position
of the tire

Right. Seems unavoidable. I planned not to repair the sag dent in
the
last bus I had with one. The rest of the body and paint was passable,
but
I decided that the dent was hidden by the tire and would likely
just happen
again anyway if I fixed it.

> Problem is, I have those threaded inserts in
the holes where the emblem pins
usually go.  ...  I could drill out the
threads and use silicone to fill the
holes around the pins

I don't like
silicone because of later hassles for painting. If you
decide to use it,
smooth the face, wipe with alcohol around the holes
before the silicone sets,
and let it overflow behind for grip.

> or look at the backside of the nose
panel and see if I can remove the
inserts, has anyone done this and if so,
how?

That's a notoriously difficult area to get your fingers to. A real
challenge even for just changing an emblem.

> On a related note, I spent a
good half hour at the local  wall of fasteners
looking for a match for the one
screw I had that fit the inserts.  Problem
was, I was looking in the metric
section and I later found the insert was a
10-24 thread!  Didn't see that one
coming!

Typical for made in the USA VW accessories. Why not just keep it
simple and plug your inserts with well-greased bolts?

Have fun,

John
